review_blob: I hate to knock what most folks are calling a great beer, but you shouldnt be able to tell the alcohol content in a dopplebock quite as strongly as this. Its not a higher alcohol thing, nothing like that, its a mouthfeel and body issue that seems to be knocking it for me. That and an overall sweetness that I just cant get past. Sure, decent maltiness and along the right flavor lines, but way too sweet and filling

Not quite as bad as some folks here are saying it is, though Im picking it up relatively close to the brewery, perhaps it doesnt travel well. 

Certainly a interesting brew, strangely sweet with a bit of roast and finally some smokiness coming through on the afternotes. Im certainly only having one, but its an interesting one nonetheless.

Light and citrusy, with enough bitterness to cover a thin body without being overwhelming. Body very light, pours crystal clear straw-gold with no head. Citrus and floral notes, quite enjoyable, especially at 6.5%

I wouldnt kick it out of bed, and especially at 1.9%, Id be willing to go a couple rounds. What it lacks in mouthfeel it compensates with in bitterness and high carbonation, stripping the palate down, but leaving no residual aftertaste.
Just all around not so hot, except the solvents alcohol, that's a little hot. Way vegetal with little/no aroma, it's a Homebrew gone wrong.
beer_name: Spanish Peaks Chugs Private Stash Big Bite IPA

review_blob: Absolutely a fantastic complex brew. Nose has all the characteristics of an old ale, dark fruit, raisins, alcohol. Flavors along similar lines with a nice spiciness to support. Carbonated wonderfully, just enough to lift the beer and clear the palate to let the next sip roll across fully. Wonderful body, an all around fantastic beer... Especially wonderful to find for 6.99 at Whole Foods
Hides its nice dark roasty backbone extremely well, nice dark malt character balanced perfectly with sweet hop notes leading to a nice light, almost lemony finish.

beer_name: Struise Pannept - Old Monks Ale - Pannepeut

review_blob: Pretty fantastic little table beer. Full pillowy white head leaps out of the glass, with a light-medium body, and possibly a little too much carbonic bite from high carbonation. Overall, good, with similar spice notes to the classic Saison DuPont.
